The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
		 Sunday, November 30, 2003  BRIEFS
				 																																	Siliguri, Nov. 29: Kamtapur Liberation Organisation (KLO) militant Pabitra Kumar Singha, alias Pavel Dev, was arrested from Panitanki near here this afternoon. 				 																																	Singha, wanted by the police for a long time, had come to meet his family from his hideout in Bihar when police were tipped off by local residents, Siliguri additional superintendent of police Rajeev Mishra said. 				 																																	Krishnagar: The Nadia district sessions court has sentenced Suresh Hazra, a BSF jawan, to life imprisonment for burning his wife, Lopamudra, alive six years ago as her family had failed to meet his dowry demands. 				 																																	Bolpur: Several long-distance trains were delayed near here as train services were disrupted in Eastern Railways Sahebgunj loop line on Saturday when the engine of a goods train jumped rails near Ahmedpur station.
